From: Claims
Sent: Tuesday, September 2, 2025 9:21 AM
To: Raffaella del Prete <raffaellanz@icloud.com<mailto:raffaellanz@icloud.c=
om>>
Subject: RE: REFUND Request : Contents Tower Claim: C90306256

Good morning, Raffaella.

I hope you are well this morning.

You will receive the $9,000 temporary accommodation payment in 3 to 5 worki=
ng days.

The remaining amount under the temporary accommodation benefit is $13,820.62

Is there a time I can contact you this week by phone to finalize your conte=
nts claim? the loss schedule provided by Asset Restore to date exceeds your=
 sum insured, which means that the contents is a total loss as the total va=
lue of the contents damaged or destroyed is greater then the sum insured. I=
 work until 1:30 so let me know when this week suits you.

I have confirmation that your privacy request and the information you reque=
sted was emailed to you on the 25/07/25. If you can check this date and let=
 me know if you have it.

Regarding updates, I am more then happy to update you on the first of each =
month, would you prefer monthly contacts from me instead of fortnightly?

Regarding further claim files, we can send you assessor reports as we recei=
ve these from the assessor. It would be less prudent for us to resend you t=
he entire claim file each month and not efficient for us due to the time it=
 takes to action these we may end up getting assessor reports during this p=
rocess which means that report may not be added to that privacy request.

Future assessor reports should be the only documents we have that you are n=
ot given by the assessor as this would come from us.

Kind regards,

Zach
