On 3 Jul 2025, at 11:27=E2=80=AFAM, Claims <Claims@tower.co.nz<mailto:Claim=
s@tower.co.nz>> wrote:
=EF=BB=BF
Good Morning Raffaella

Thank you for your emails and apologies for the delay in responding to you.

Firstly, to acknowledge the Privacy request has been received and passed on=
to our Privacy Team.

Also acknowledging that you wish all correspondence to be via email.

I am aware that you have met on site at your property yesterday with Grant =
Metson and that as proposed Tower will send you the documented process.

In addition to this I have reviewed the information with regards to the exp=
enses and can confirm the following will be paid under your Temporary Accom=
modation Benefit (limit of $30,000.00 which is the higher of the two policy=
 benefits)

$1,452.00            6 nights Esplanade Hotel
$5,000.00           Rent @ $1,000.00 per week
$727.38               Moving costs to temp accommodation

$7,179.38           Total of Temporary Accommodation benefit used to date.

The other two payments as follows will be under your Contents claim as part=
 of your sum insured.

$340                     cleaning of clothes
$454.25               cleaning of sofa


With regards to your query if Stress Benefit applies, unfortunately it only=
 applies if the property and/or Contents is a Total Loss as per following p=
olicy wording, if the contents are deemed a total loss then we will proacti=
vely let you know of any changes to your eligibility for this benefit.

House
Stress benefit lump sum payment
We=E2=80=99ll pay you a lump sum for the stress caused to you if your entir=
e house is destroyed.
We pay this benefit in addition to your sum insured.
Limit
We=E2=80=99ll pay a maximum of $1,000 for each event as soon as we=E2=80=99=
ve accepted your house claim

Contents
Stress benefit lump sum payment
We=E2=80=99ll pay you a lump sum for the stress caused to you if all your c=
ontents are destroyed.
This benefit is in addition to your contents sum insured.
Limit
We=E2=80=99ll pay a maximum of $2,000 for each event as soon as we have acc=
epted your contents
claim.

Please advise if you are happy for these payments to be made to your nomina=
ted account on file where the premiums are deducted from or wish to supply =
an alternative account.

Just reach out if you have any further questions as always, I am happy to a=
ssist.

Kind Regards



Sasha C
Claims Consultant | Tower
DDI: 09 369 0583
PO Box 90347, Auckland 1142
claims@tower.co.nz<mailto:claims@tower.co.nz> | tower.co.nz<http://www.towe=
r.co.nz/>

